FBIS3-60849 "jptot001__l94097" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given Hijackers To Kill Hostage if Ransom Not Received AU2412095493 Paris AFP in English 0947 GMT 24 Dec 93 AU2412095493 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow, Dec 24 (AFP) -- Four heavily-armed men holding 11 hostages including nine children aboard a helicopter threatened Friday to kill one of the hostages if they did not receive a $10 million ransom, an air force spokesman told AFP. The helicopter took off from the spa town of Mineralnyye Vody earlier, apparently heading for an unknown destination, but returned and has been hovering over the airport since then, the spokesman said.
